# Project Structure and Entry Points

This project is full-stack Next.js (no separate Express/Node backend). Key locations:

- `app shell` → [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx)
- `root route` → [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx)
- `global styles` → [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- `api routes` → [src/app/api](mdc:src/app/api)
- `prisma schema` → [prisma/schema.prisma](mdc:prisma/schema.prisma)
- `public assets` → [public/](mdc:public)
- `config` → [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts), [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json), [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs)
- `readme & guide` → [README.md](mdc:README.md)

Guiding principles from the docs:

- Use Server Components by default for data reads.
- Use Server Actions for mutations initiated from the client.
- Use Route Handlers for webhooks or public APIs.

Organize features under `src/` as follows (when adding files):

- `src/actions` for Server Actions
- `src/components/ui` for base UI
- `src/components/features` for domain components
- `src/lib` for utilities (e.g., Prisma client singleton)

